The paper deals with the representation and analysis of multidimensional data, which is a common topic in database research (cs.DB). The use of OLAP techniques and the development of a query language suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of RDF and SPARQL, as well as the focus on optimization, suggest a connection to deep learning (cs.DL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
